titleproper.value: Guide to the New York University Archives Photograph Collection

titlestmt.author: Finding aid prepared by David O'Neill and Lisa Darms.

Updated by Jacqueline Rider to include previously undescribed materials in University
          Archives,

Collection level description updated by John Zarrillo to account for previously
          undescribed materials in University Archives

abstract.value:
The collection contains photographs
        that document the history of New York University and it surrounding environs, especially
        Washington Square Park and Greenwich Village. It includes images associated with NYU's
        various component schools and its former University Heights campus (now Bronx Community
        College).

p.value:
This series contains photographs and prints of the interior and exterior of the
            University Building as well as the immediate surrounding area.

"The University Building." The University Quarterly 17 (May 1894): 116-123. "University
            Building." New York University Education Quarterly (Spring 1981): 20.

The photos are arranged by type of view (exterior and interior). Exterior views are
            arranged chronologically. Interior views are arranged by subject (type of room).

p.value:
The collection contains photographs that document the history of New York University and it
        surrounding environs, especially Washington Square Park and Greenwich Village. It includes
        images associated with NYU's various component schools and its former University Heights
        campus (now Bronx Community College).

"The University Building." The University Quarterly 17 (May 1894): 116-123. "University
        Building." New York University Education Quarterly (Spring 1981): 20.
Materials are open without restrictions.

Because of the assembled nature of this collection, copyright status varies across the
        collection. Copyrights held by original creators of individual items in the collection are
        expected to pass into the public domain 120 years after their creation. For more
        information, contact New York University Archives, (212) 998-2646,
        university-archives@nyu.edu.

In May 2019, previously undescribed materials were added to the finding aid, and boxes for
        the entire collection were renumbered in numerical order.
The collection is organized into 33 series.
